{"name": "find_in_field_order_limit_offset_midslice", "surfaces": ["api", "axilql"], "known_divergence": "Field-scoped FTS ORDER BY is a global sort on both surfaces here: AxilQL FIND ... IN <field> fetches up to max(LIMIT,100) hits then sorts the full set before OFFSET/LIMIT, and the api surface ports that exact pipeline over db.search_field — so both deterministically return [i3,i4]. The DIVERGENT path this case documents is plain FIND (no IN) / QueryBuilder search_text().order_by().limit().offset(), which routes through exec_fts: it caps candidates at limit+offset in FTS-score order BEFORE the ORDER BY sort, so when limit+offset < match count its ORDER BY is a window sort, not a global one, and can return different rows. That path is not a surface of this case; the note pins the asymmetry until exec_fts sorts before capping.", "setup": [{"insert": {"as": "i1", "table": "items", "data": {"body": "widget", "n": 1}}}, {"insert": {"as": "i2", "table": "items", "data": {"body": "widget", "n": 2}}}, {"insert": {"as": "i3", "table": "items", "data": {"body": "widget", "n": 3}}}, {"insert": {"as": "i4", "table": "items", "data": {"body": "widget", "n": 4}}}, {"insert": {"as": "i5", "table": "items", "data": {"body": "widget", "n": 5}}}], "op": {"kind": "fts", "query": "widget", "field": "body", "order_by": {"field": "n", "dir": "asc"}, "limit": 2, "offset": 2}, "expect": {"outcome": "records", "ordered": true, "records": ["i3", "i4"]}}
